Visulization 1

Caption: This visualization combines a scatter plot and a bar chart. The scatter plot illustrates the relationship between the percentage of Black students in a school and their graduation rate. By selecting a percentage range on the x-axis or clicking on a specific year, the bar chart on the right will display the average Regents exam scores for both Black and White students within the selected range. The green line and shadow box indicate that schools with a lower percentage of Black students are more likely to show better academic performance for Black students. Additionally, in schools with a higher percentage of White students, both Black and White students tend to achieve higher academic performance, with White students generally outperforming Black students.

Visulization 2

Caption: The Diversity Index is calculated using the Shannon Index based on the number of enrolled students from different ethnicities. This figure combines a line plot showing the change in diversity from 2001 to 2020 in NYC. A histogram displays the distribution of the Diversity Index for the selected year, which can be chosen by hovering over a specific point on the line plot. The two red vertical lines highlight two key policy changes related to diversity.
